populateObject

private static <T> void populateObject(T subject,
                                       java.util.Map<java.lang.Class<?>,UsedInfo<?>> knownInstances)
Populates given object with dummy value. The behavior can vary depending on the type of object, as follows:
  • Collection: if the type is a subtype of Collection, a random number of items, 1 or 2, will be added
  • Map: if the type is a subtype of Map, a random number of key/value entries, 1 or 2, will be added
  • Other types: The setter methods will be retrieved from the object and will be invoked with a new dummy value.

Parameters:
subject - The object to populate with dummy values.
knownInstances - A list of known instances to keep track of already processed classes (to avoid infinite loop)
See Also:
createDummyOfClass(Class, Map)
